2:
Sing to him; praise him as you sing to him;
\q2 tell others about his wonderful miracles.
\q1

8:
He never forgets the covenant that he made;
\q2 he made a promise that will last for a thousand generations.
\q1

20:
The king of Egypt sent servants, who set him free;
\q2 this ruler released Joseph from prison.
\q1

30:
Then he caused the land to become full of frogs;
\q2 the king and his officials even had frogs in their bedrooms.
\q1

34:
He commanded locusts to come, and hordes of them came;
\q2 so many came that they could not be counted.
\q1

39:
Then Yahweh spread a cloud to cover the Israelites;
\q2 and at night it became a big fire in the sky to give them light.
\q1

43:
So his people were joyful as he brought them out from Egypt;
\q2 these people whom he had chosen were shouting joyfully as they went.
\q1
